.TH PACKAGE 1 "DATE" "version VERSION" ""
.SH NAME
PACKAGE \- overwrite files with zeros and delete them.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B PACKAGE
[filespecs] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
The PACKAGE program overwrites the contents of all the files it has been
given as arguments with zeros and unlinks them.
.SH OPTIONS
This programs takes no options.
.SH FILES
There are no files associated with this program.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
The following messages can be generated on the console:
.TP 0
.I rrm cannot allocate memory
A call to 
.BR calloc (3)
failed.
.TP 0
.I rrm cannot open <filename>
A call to 
.BR fopen (3) 
failed.
.TP 0
.I rrm cannot seek to end-of-file
A call to 
.BR fseek (3) 
failed.
.TP 0
.I rrm cannot establish the size of <filename>
A call to 
.BR ftell (3)
failed.
.TP 0
.I rrm cannot unlink <filename>
A call to 
.BR unlink (2)
failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR calloc (3),
.BR fopen (3), 
.BR fseek (3), 
.BR ftell (3),
.BR unlink (2),
DOCSDIR/README
.SH BUGS
The names of overwritten files are contained in the filesystem
datastructures and are not overwritten.
